b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Automation Anywhere is best suited for large enterprises, IT operations, shared services, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Salesforce Flow, meanwhile, shines for Salesforce admins, enterprises, sales operations, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2003, Automation Anywhere describes itself as \"Enterprise RPA platform combining bots, AI, and process intelligence.\" Salesforce Flow, established in 1999, positions itself as \"Salesforce's declarative automation engine for complex business processes.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Automation Anywhere** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0). However, this does not mean Salesforce Flow is a poor choice — far from it. Salesforce Flow excels in its own right, particularly for Salesforce admins and enterprises.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value market-leading rpa capabilities, go with Automation Anywhere. If extremely powerful for salesforce automation matters more to you, Salesforce Flow is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
